channel.title: Bit of inspiration, take a look
channel.description:

item.title: Bit of inspiration, take a look
item.dc:creator: @SilentCJ SilentCJ
item.description:
@SilentCJ wrote:

badger41:

this is a great model, but dont electric guitars usually have knobs on the face too?

Still got them to do, it’s still in development, not finished.

[quote=“the elve age, post:8, topic:341611”]Eww. It doesn’t look like a well built guitar (if it was real)

Why are the tuners on the back? The face of the guitar is plane and ugly.
The body and bridges are way to far apart.
The end of the neck is suppose to be a bit more round, not straight flat.

You need to add volume & tone control, and guitar input

The nut and headstock, look to straight and plane (the end of the guitar)

But good job, if its not done ;)[/quote]

Tuners on the back?
Yes, I’m working the main body texture again when I’ve got all the geometry done.
Bridges? Guitars only have one, of which mine is not finished. Can’t possibly be out of place either as I used a reference image.

This is a slimline neck, therefore the end is very thin. This particular design of the Ibanez was built to be slimline, the SA series.

Yes, they will be added once the bridge is finished, as I said, it’s still in development.

Read full topic
